=\"/blog\">Blog</a></div><a class=\"inline-flex min-h-11 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-ink px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-bold text-white transition hover:-translate-y-0.5\" href=\"/create\">Start a Book</a></nav></header><main><section class=\"page-shell py-16\"><p class=\"font-bold text-sage text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-4\">Samples</p><h1 class=\"display text-5xl font-bold mb-4\">What a finished book looks like.</h1><p class=\"text-ink/65 text-lg leading-8 max-w-xl\">Real chapters and illustrations from completed PageCub books — two different illustration styles, same character, two different stories.</p></section><section class=\"py-16 \"><div class=\"page-shell\"><div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 mb-10\"><div><span class=\"inline-block rounded-full border border-honey/50 bg-honey/10 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-bold text-honey mb-2\">Style: <!-- -->Bright colorful modern</span><h2 class=\"display text-3xl font-bold\">Aurelia and the Moonlight Kingdom</h2><p class=\"text-ink/55 text-sm mt-1\">Character: <!-- -->Aurelia</p></div></div><div class=\"space-y-12\"><div class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"px-7 py-5 border-b border-line\"><p class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sage mb-1\">Chapter <!-- -->1</p><h3 class=\"display text-2xl font-bold\">Not Sleepy Yet</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-ink/50 mt-1 italic\">Aurelia is bursting with energy at bedtime and tells Mama she cannot possibly sleep because she heard a dragon outside her window.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 \"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center \"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">Aurelia was NOT sleepy. Not even a little bit.\n\nShe stood in her favorite yellow dress and her rainbow rainboots. Her brown hair tumbled past her shoulders, curling at the tips, half of it flopping right over one eye the way it always did.\n\nShe bounced on her toes. She wiggled her fingers. She made a silly face at her stuffed bunny.</p></div><div class=\"\"><img alt=\"Not Sleepy Yet — illustration 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F9c16f3e2-632d-432a-858a-4cac45f62abc.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 md:[direction:rtl]\"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center md:[direction:ltr]\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">&quot;Bedtime, sweet girl!&quot; Mama called from the doorway.\n\nAurelia leaned in close, like she had the most important secret in the whole world. She cupped her hands around her mouth and whispered very loudly.\n\n&quot;But Mama,&quot; she said, &quot;I can&#x27;t go to bed yet! I think I heard a DRAGON outside!&quot;</p></div><div class=\"md:[direction:ltr]\"><img alt=\"Not Sleepy Yet — illustration 2\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F3ff76772-2259-4669-8601-0a4ddbbd4732.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div></div><div class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"px-7 py-5 border-b border-line\"><p class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sage mb-1\">Chapter <!-- -->3</p><h3 class=\"display text-2xl font-bold\">A Tiny Dragon Friend</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-ink/50 mt-1 italic\">Aurelia climbs through her window onto the golden path and meets a tiny friendly dragon who lands on her shoulder.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 \"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center \"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">Aurelia giggled and climbed right through the window onto the sparkly golden path.\n\nHer rainbow rainboots went crunch, crunch on the glittering ground. The air smelled like warm cookies and fresh rain all swirled together.\n\nTiny star-flowers tickled her ankles as she walked.</p></div><div class=\"\"><img alt=\"A Tiny Dragon Friend — illustration 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fb4bcb09e-a0f2-4ec4-8a9f-434c3f2991f1.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 md:[direction:rtl]\"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center md:[direction:ltr]\"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">A tiny dragon landed right on her shoulder!\n\nHe was no bigger than a kitten, with shimmery green and gold scales and big round eyes that blinked at her. His little wings folded up neatly against his back.\n\n&quot;Hello!&quot; said Aurelia. The dragon tilted his head. Then he purred, soft and rumbly, like a happy cat.</p></div><div class=\"md:[direction:ltr]\"><img alt=\"A Tiny Dragon Friend — illustration 2\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2F74aca76d-d514-414c-957b-a5984c77f9ed.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-16 bg-sage/8\"><div class=\"page-shell\"><div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4 mb-10\"><div><span class=\"inline-block rounded-full border border-honey/50 bg-honey/10 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-bold text-honey mb-2\">Style: <!-- -->Whimsical fantasy</span><h2 class=\"display text-3xl font-bold\">Aurelia and the New School</h2><p class=\"text-ink/55 text-sm mt-1\">Character: <!-- -->Aurelia</p></div></div><div class=\"space-y-12\"><div class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"px-7 py-5 border-b border-line\"><p class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sage mb-1\">Chapter <!-- -->1</p><h3 class=\"display text-2xl font-bold\">Rainbow Boots and Butterflies</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-ink/50 mt-1 italic\">Aurelia wakes up on the first day of a brand new school, nervous and excited all at once.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 \"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center \"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">Aurelia opened her eyes and sat right up in bed.\n\nToday was the day. A brand new school.\n\nShe wiggled her fingers under the covers. Her tummy felt fizzy — like ginger ale and butterflies all mixed together.</p></div><div class=\"\"><img alt=\"Rainbow Boots and Butterflies — illustration 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Ff2c21988-d0df-4c97-8c21-7a6b66dce385.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Ff2c21988-d0df-4c97-8c21-7a6b66dce385.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Ff2c21988-d0df-4c97-8c21-7a6b66dce385.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div></div><div class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"px-7 py-5 border-b border-line\"><p class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sage mb-1\">Chapter <!-- -->2</p><h3 class=\"display text-2xl font-bold\">The Ride to School</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-ink/50 mt-1 italic\">The whole family piles into the car for the drive to school.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 \"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center \"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">Everybody piled into the car.\n\nPapa buckled his seatbelt and started the engine. Mama turned around and smiled that smile — the one that meant everything was going to be okay.\n\nAurelia pressed her face against the window and watched the streets go by.</p></div><div class=\"\"><img alt=\"The Ride to School — illustration 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fbf6794a5-f04b-4129-9f24-5865dcadd897.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fbf6794a5-f04b-4129-9f24-5865dcadd897.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fbf6794a5-f04b-4129-9f24-5865dcadd897.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"/></div></div></div><div class=\"rounded-[2rem] border border-line bg-card overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"px-7 py-5 border-b border-line\"><p class=\"text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-sage mb-1\">Chapter <!-- -->3</p><h3 class=\"display text-2xl font-bold\">The Big Bright Doors</h3><p class=\"text-sm text-ink/50 mt-1 italic\">Aurelia stands at the bottom of the school steps and takes a deep breath.</p></div><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 \"><div class=\"p-7 flex items-center \"><p class=\"text-sm leading-8 text-ink/80 whitespace-pre-line\">Aurelia stood at the bottom of the steps.\n\nThe preschool doors were big and bright. Someone had painted sunflowers on them. She counted the petals without meaning to.\n\nHer hand found Papa&#x27;s hand. She held on tight.</p></div><div class=\"\"><img alt=\"The Big Bright Doors — illustration 1\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"720\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"aspect-square w-full object-cover\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd1ed5746-678c-42b4-9e27-d9129a51780d.webp&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 1x, /_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd1ed5746-678c-42b4-9e27-d9129a51780d.webp&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.mscdn.ai%2F1421a93f-f05c-4d19-9184-e2af13b48c41%2Fgenerated-images%2Fd1e